main event: An unidentified flying object was reported in Centerville, Ohio on August 27, 1950, appearing as a star that moved from side to side.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for approximately 5 to 7 minutes,The object did not disappear while being observed,It was described as having characteristics similar to a star but was believed to be moving,The analysis ruled out known astronomical phenomena such as meteors or planets,The sighting was reported to the U.S. Air Force Technical Information Sheet.
witness description: Anonymous, details on personal information were not provided.
